23/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Gjirokastra announced on Tuesday (March 22nd) they have seized 200kg of cocaine purportedly bound from Colombia to Spain and other countries in the region. 
A businessman in the southern city of Gjirokastra was arrested, as well as two Macedonian citizens who allegedly hid the drugs in an oil truck. 
Police acted on information provided by Belgian and Spanish counterparts against what may turn out to be a powerful international drug trafficking ring. 
(Top Channel, Balkan Web, VoA, Lajmifundit, Top News, Klan - 22/03/11)
